<body class="px-page">

  <%- include("partials/nav") %>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="px-page-hero center">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-eyebrow">About Aquiplex</div>
      <h1>One system that plans, reasons, and executes.</h1>
      <p>Aquiplex is an AI Operating System. At its core is Aqua — a memory-driven intelligence that turns goals into finished work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">

  <!-- Why -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">Why we exist</div>
        <h2>The problem isn't a lack of AI. It's a lack of execution.</h2>
        <p>Chatbots answer questions and hand the work back to you. We built Aquiplex around a different idea: one intelligence that carries your context, plans the path, and delivers the result — code, documents, projects — inside a single workspace.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="px-steps">
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Memory</span>
          <h3>Context that compounds</h3>
          <p>Aqua remembers your projects, preferences, and constraints across every session — so you never explain yourself twice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Planning</span>
          <h3>Goals become steps</h3>
          <p>Every request is decomposed into a concrete plan, verified against your intent before a single step runs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-step px-reveal">
          <span class="px-step-num">Execution</span>
          <h3>Real outputs, delivered</h3>
          <p>Websites, applications, research, and documents land in your workspace — versioned, previewable, and ready to ship.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Aquiplex is -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">The platform</div>
        <h2>Everything revolves around Aqua.</h2>
        <p>Aquiplex isn't a collection of tools. It's one product — a workspace where chat, projects, files, and knowledge share a single memory and a single execution engine.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="px-feature-grid px-reveal">
        <div class="px-feature">
          <div class="px-feature-icon"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M2 3h12v8H6l-3 3v-3H2V3z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Aqua AI</h3>
          <p>The flagship. A reasoning, streaming, memory-driven assistant that plans before it acts and verifies before it answers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-feature">
          <div class="px-feature-icon"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><rect x="2" y="2" width="12" height="12" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/><path d="M2 6h12M6 6v8" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Projects</h3>
          <p>Describe a goal and Aqua builds the plan, executes each step, and can turn the result into a deployed site or app.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-feature">
          <div class="px-feature-icon"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none"><path d="M3 2h7l3 3v9H3V2z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linejoin="round"/><path d="M10 2v3h3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Knowledge</h3>
          <p>Upload codebases, PDFs, spreadsheets, and decks. Aqua ingests them, reasons over them, and proposes precise, reviewable changes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="px-section">
    <div class="px-container">
      <div class="px-sec-head px-reveal">
        <div class="px-eyebrow">Principles</div>
        <h2>How we build</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="px-feature-grid px-reveal">
        <div class="px-feature">
          <h3>Results over suggestions</h3>
          <p>If Aqua can do the work, it should do the work. The unit of value is a finished output, not a paragraph of advice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-feature">
          <h3>Simple, honest pricing</h3>
          <p>Free credits every day. Prepaid packs that never expire. No subscriptions, no lock-in, no surprises.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="px-feature">
          <h3>One coherent product</h3>
          <p>One design system, one memory, one workspace. Every surface of Aquiplex should feel like the same product — because it is.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <hr class="px-waterline" aria-hidden="true">
  <section class="px-cta">
    <div class="px-container px-reveal">
      <h2>See what Aqua can do.</h2>
      <p>Your workspace is ready in under a minute.</p>
      <div class="px-btn-row center">
        <a href="/signup" class="px-btn px-btn-primary px-btn-lg">Get started free</a>
        <a href="/founders" class="px-btn px-btn-secondary px-btn-lg">Meet the founders</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include("partials/footer") %>

  <script>
    (function () {
      if (!('IntersectionObserver' in window)) {
        document.querySelectorAll('.px-reveal').forEach(function (el) { el.classList.add('in'); });
        return;
      }
      var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
        entries.forEach(function (e) {
          if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('in'); io.unobserve(e.target); }
        });
      }, { threshold: 0.12 });
      document.querySelectorAll('.px-reveal').forEach(function (el) { io.observe(el); });
    })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
